HEADWORD: Abanga
<hw>A*ban"ga</hw> <pr>(⟦adot⟧*b⟦acr⟧⟦nsm⟧"g⟦adot⟧)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Name given by the negroes in the island of St.
Thomas.]</ety> <def>A West Indian palm; also the fruit of this palm, the
seeds of which are used as a remedy for diseases of the chest.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

